The paper deals with weight distributions of linear codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the weight distributions of codes over finite fields, which is relevant to cryptography (cs.CR). The use of simplex codes and MDS codes suggests a focus on coding theory (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the rearrangement of codewords, which could be related to data structures (cs.DS) or signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the derivation of symbol $b$-weight distributions could be relevant to network information theory (cs.NI).
